                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/143.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reported to me last night by member of mining committee that mine operators of
                    Chihuahua had been called upon by Villa for loan of $300,000 gold, which has
                    been refused. They fear this refusal may cause authorities to put mining decree
                    in force notwithstanding Escudero’s circular, which has not been published as
                    promised. I have telegraphed Escudero requesting him to publish it in today’s
                    issue of the official paper.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
